library(caret)
## Loading required package: lattice
## Loading required package: ggplot2

library("e1071")
library(data.table)
library(FastKNN)
#we combine the information of X, Y and Z coordinates colunmwise and scale the data since distances are calculated
train<-cbind(Xmat,Ymat[,-1],Zmat[,-1])
train[,-1]=scale(train[,-1])
test<-cbind(Xtestmat,Ytestmat[,-1],Ztestmat[,-1])
test[,-1]=scale(test[,-1])
require(TunePareto)
## Loading required package: TunePareto
k_levels=c(1,3,5,7,9)
#calculation of distance matrices
manhattan= as.matrix(dist(train[,-1], method = "manhattan"))
euclidean= as.matrix(dist(train[,-1], method = "euclidean"))
nofReplications=1
nFolds=10
indices=generateCVRuns(train[,1],nofReplications,nFolds,stratified=TRUE)
#we perform 10 cross validation to determine the best k value for manhattan distance
cvresult=data.table()
for(i in 1:nofReplications) 
{
  thisReplication=indices[[i]]
  for(j in 1:nFolds)
  {
    testindices=thisReplication[[j]]
    cvtrain=train[-testindices,]        
    cvtest=train[testindices,]
    labels<-as.numeric(rownames(as.data.table(cvtrain)))
    for(y in 1:length(k_levels))
    {
      param_k=k_levels[y]
      predict_knn = knn_test_function(cvtrain, cvtest, manhattan[testindices,labels], train[,1], k = param_k)
      cvresult=rbind(cvresult,data.table(Replication=i,Fold=j,Method='knn',Klev=param_k,TestId=testindices,
                                         Predictions=as.numeric(as.character(predict_knn)),Real=train[testindices,1]))
    }   
  }    
}
#accuracies for different k values
cvresult[,list(Accu=mean(Predictions==Real)),by=list(Method,Klev)]
##    Method Klev      Accu
## 1:    knn    1 0.9553571
## 2:    knn    3 0.9542411
## 3:    knn    5 0.9508929
## 4:    knn    7 0.9430804
## 5:    knn    9 0.9363839
#see that the best k level is 3
manhattan_k=3

#we perform 10 cross validation to determine the best k value for euclidean distance
cvresult=data.table()
for(i in 1:nofReplications) 
  {
  thisReplication=indices[[i]]
  for(j in 1:nFolds)
    {
    testindices=thisReplication[[j]]
    cvtrain=train[-testindices,]        
    cvtest=train[testindices,]
    labels<-as.numeric(rownames(as.data.table(cvtrain)))
    for(y in 1:length(k_levels))
      {
      param_k=k_levels[y]
      predict_knn = knn_test_function(cvtrain, cvtest, euclidean[testindices,labels], train[,1], k = param_k)

                                       Predictions=as.numeric(as.character(predict_knn)),Real=train[testindices,1]))
    }   
  }    
}

euclideanprediction<-c()
for(i in 1:nrow(test))
{   
  euclidean_dist =c()         
  for(j in 1:nrow(train))
  {
    euclidean_dist[j]=dist(rbind(test[i,-1], train[j,-1]),method="euclidean")
  }
  nntable = data.frame(train[,1], euclidean_dist) 
  nntable = nntable[order(nntable$euclidean_dist ),]      
  nntable = nntable[c(1:euclidean_k),]       
  euclideanprediction[i]=as.numeric(names(which.max(table(nntable[,1])))) 
}
